    "Id": "848579",
    "ThreadId": "359257",
    "Html": "<p>Hi Jens,</p>\r\n<p>I have downloaded you repro-sample application, but I couldn't reproduce the issue you are mentioning.</p>\r\n<p>I tried running the application with the <strong>MenuView </strong>(which uses the <strong>MenuControl </strong>defined in the <strong>Ar.Base.Controls</strong> project) and the <strong>MenuViewDirect </strong>(which contains its own menu.) In both cases, the commands of each menu item where invoked correctly. We have checked this by setting a <em><strong>breakpoint</strong></em>, in the <strong>MenuSelected </strong>method of the <strong>MenuViewModel </strong>class.</p>\r\n<p>Based on this, I believe the problem you are describing may be related to the your environment rather that the code. As a possible approach you could try cleaning you solution (by pressing <strong>Clean Solution</strong> in the <strong>Build </strong>menu), deleting the <strong>obj </strong>and <strong>Bin </strong>folders of each project and deleting the files contained in the <strong>ClientBin </strong>folder of the <strong>Ag.Web</strong> project, so that the next time you run the application, it will be built again.</p>\r\n<p>Regards,</p>\r\n<p>Damian Cherubini<br /> <a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/dcherubini\">http://blogs.southworks.net/dcherubini</a></p>",
